rComments: He is a funny prof and responds quickly to emails, but for a second year class, its workload is wayyy too heavy. As a fourth year student, this is one of the heaviest workloads I have had. Gives two projects 10+ page projects on two 600 page books. Do the math. I heavily suggest anyone to take the English version of this class as it is much easier.
He was funny, extremely interesting and very knowlegable. I miss his classes.

He's a good person and is very accessible (i.e replies to emails fast) Although the project questions are pretty dense and are harder to understand. In his lectures, the power points don't have much info on them and it's hard to keep up with where he is going. If he had a few handouts or explanation then it would be a more enjoyable class.

His classes are pretty interesting and the guy is really funny. On the other hand, his PowerPoints are very long (100 and something slides) and you really have to put some efforts to succeed. The final project needed a lot of research and I had to spend lots of time at the library. So be ready to work to earn your grade

Si vous pensez prendre ce cours ou prof pour un cours option facile ; non. Les pp ne sont vraiment pas clairs, beaucoup de photos mais pas d'explication. Les lectures sont vraiment abstraites et parfois difficile à comprendre Très difficile à satisfaire pour les projets et peu d'explication. Très bonne personne mais je ne recommande pas le cours.
He talks rather quickly so if you're more of a visual type of person, recording the classes help a lot. And unless you don't prep for exams or assignments well in advance, you'll most likely fail.
tough grader, not a bird course. there's a woman that also teach the same course take her instead way easier. ppt as lots of pictures and not enough info.

He might just be the best professor that ever lived! He is a great scholar and great at communicating the material. He is kind and sincere. I hope you will be as lucky as I was to have him as a professor.
Great class, he's a fantastic teacher, his exams are fair and he's a good grader. Work hard, study hard, and it'll really pay off!

Best teacher ever.... he restored my faith in university profs. Take all of his classes if possible, even if french isn't your first language, he is definitely worth it. Very funny, makes learning anything fun, I miss him!
Good Prof! Super funny, dynamic...suggest taking his classes

Amazing prof. Had a blast taking his classes and I realize how important it is to have a good prof now that most of my profs can't compare. He had a really good connection with the students and was always there to help.

Best teacher ever!!! He explains so well and makes it so easy to learn.  I loved him!! And it helps that he is very good looking!!!!
Amaizing!! Such a good teacher! tests are so easy because he explains so well!
